body: @bulatyauheni Bazel does not support Android on Windows yet. You might try the [cmake build](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/contrib/android/cmake), but easiest thing to do if you just want to plug something into your Android Studio project is to grab the pre-built libraries referenced above.
